g.title: Ruler is an instrument for measuring thelinear lengths. One dash shows 30 km (18.6 mi), approximate distance of a daily loaded march. Drag edge circles to move the ruler, center circle to split the ruler into 2 parts. Click on the ruler label to remove the ruler from the map
Map scale defines ratio between distance on a map and the corresponding distance on the ground. Click to edit the map scale, drag to move the bar
